  "original_title": "\u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0dc4\u0dd0\u0d82\u0d9c\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dbb \u0dad\u0dd4\u0db1\u0d9a \u0d85\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dc0\u0dd6 \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0daf\u0dac\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A three-year suspended sentence for fuel storage",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Anuradhapura Additional Magistrate Mrs. Rudrika De Silva Hevawasam, who pleaded guilty to the charge of concealing fuel stocks and making false statements about the lack of fuel to consumers and not selling the fuel he had, sentenced the manager of a fuel station on Airport Road, Anuradhapura to three months imprisonment. ordered.",
        "In addition, the Additional Magistrate who fined the owner of the fuel station Rs. 10,000, warned the accused not to make such mistakes again and if it is reported to the court that such mistakes are made, the court will take strict action in this regard.",
        "Sinhalese Wijekumara, the manager of Indika Fuel Station on Airport Road, Anuradhapura, was sentenced.",
        "Mr. Indunil Hettiarach, the lawyer who appeared for the suspect, gave his basic facts and informed that the fuel stocks were kept for the needs of specialist doctors as per the request made by the director of Anuradhapura Teaching Hospital.",
        "However, the lawyer told the court that the defendant agreed to plead guilty and end this case briefly.",
        "Speaking to the court on behalf of the plaintiffs, Mr. BAC P Perera, Senior Investigative Officer of the Anuradhapura District Office of the Consumer Affairs Authority, said that neither a hospital director nor any other external party has the legal right to order that the stock of fuel be retained for the needs of various parties without selling it to the consumers. means",
        "Mr. Perera, who questioned whether the excess of 7,000 liters of fuel was kept hidden for the specialist doctors, said before the court that the statements of the defendants are false and they are thoroughly rejected."
      ],
